9:
Yes, this poster. This establishment
seems to be looking for a
"part-timer"... I wonder what that
would entail?
13:
That's just one type of employee.
Looks like they're looking for a
dishwasher.
17:
You mean to say that I can wash
dishes and receive a wage for it?
22:
Precisely. If you're up to it, why not
give it a try?
29:
Uh, have you ever washed a single
dish in your life?
37:
However, I have a feeling I just might
develop a knack for it!
40:
I will go ahead and apply. The rest of
you can feel free to go on without
me!
47:
Wh-what do you mean, I'm fired?
Please, I'll be more careful next time,
I swear on my honor as a Mirean—
51:
Toria, are you okay? What
happened? Did you break a plate or
something?
56:
Oh, hello, everyone...
If by "break," you mean "destroy,"
and by "plate," you mean "the whole
kitchen," then yes.
66:
I have no time for self-pity! I will
simply endeavor to do better at my
next job!
70: Seriously? You're going to try again?
75:
Why, of course! Palpebra has more
than one establishment in need of
work! I merely need to find the right
place!
78:
Aha! A posting for a waitress. Lifting
objects and cleaning? I think this job
should be more suited to my skills!
89:
Fired again... It's no use... No matter
where I go, I can't hold down a job. I'll
never be able to save up money like
this...
93:
Er, my condolences... But why
exactly are you so desperate to
save up money? Did you overspend
again?
98: No! Nothing of the sort! It's just...
102:
Never mind. I need to hurry and
search for my next employment
opportunity!
106:
Doing the same thing is probably
going to get you fired again. Just
sayin'.
116:
If you want money, can't you just
take on monster-slaying requests
from the Guild? That's what we do.
120:
Perhaps she is trying to infiltrate
Palpebran society? Life as an
adventurer is not exactly the most
social of jobs.
124:
Wait, you can get paid to slay
monsters?!
131:
Haha... Yep, you can. Monsters are
quite the nuisance for your average
person!
135:
The thought never even occurred to
me!
139:
Well, if that's the case, then I
suppose I'll have to take on as many
of these requests as I can!
143: Do you mind if we tag along?
148: But... I needed to get you—I mean...
152:
What're you mumbling about? Let's
get a move on!
159: I won't be holding back! Here I go!
163:
Oh, another pack! More money to
line my pockets with, I suppose!
169:
Boy, I'm totally spent... She really
went and picked up as many
requests as possible, huh?
172:
That she did.
Speaking of the little princess,
where'd she run off to?
176:
I do not know. She said there was a
place she wanted to stop by.
181:
Sorry to keep you waiting, my
Legendary Four!
185:
Welcome back. You seem to be in
high spirits today!
191:
I am! And do you know why? It's
because I was finally able to buy the
thing I had my eye on!
196:
Wow, this is quite the fine piece. Is
this one of the sacred relics you
were looking for?
201:
Not quite. This is... a present to all of
you! A sign of my gratitude for your
help and kindness!
206:
I see... Is this why you were looking
for work?
211:
Indeed! Well, there's no need to
hesitate—go ahead and take a look!
217:
Wh-whoa! Be careful, Toria! This is
super fragile!
221:
It's okay! I know precisely how much
strength to use when handling this
to ensure that it doesn't—
230:
I-it's no problem, Toria. Look, it broke
into five pieces, right? That's one for
each of us!
234:
If we all hold on to one piece,
together it will constitute a whole. It
can be a symbol of our unity!
238:
Where do you come up with this
stuff, Light? It's broken glass.
260:
It's in a different shape than before,
admittedly, but it's back in one piece!
265:
That's incredible, Toria. You made it
into a ball.
269:
Y-you squeezed the glass until it
turned it a ball... The amount of
strength you'd need to do that is
just...
273:
W-well, be it plate or ball, it seems
we have ourselves a present! Our
bonds remain unchanged.
277:
Precisely, Light! Now, I think a toast is
in order!
280:
Long live the kingdom of Mirea!
And finally, long live the Legendary
Four!
